node.text:
Looking to revitalize the relationships you have with the people in your life? 🧐

One of the most powerful ways to do this is to find new ways to engage! What are some fun and new activities you can do together? Any new experiences you can share?

When people are in novelty situations, their self-awareness goes up! Their mindfulness goes up! Their attentiveness goes up!

So it's time you start actively and intentionally scheduling new and exciting experiences and activities with your friends! You'll start to see how incorporating novelty into your time together will help form a deeper, more extraordinary bond!

Tag a person below and share your idea of something new you can experience together! 👇

node.text:
Are you looking to elevate your leadership skills at work or at home? 🤔

One of the biggest roadblocks I see my coaching clients hit is that their team, their family, their community — they don't have any autonomy in the vision.

As a leader, it's your duty to include others in both the creating and deciding. When people can participate and have a hand in the creating process, they will be more engaged, excited, hardworking, and excellent! Remember — people support what they create!

So how are you performing as a leader? Are you allowing others to have a real contribution and a voice in the process? This is SUCH an important question to ask yourself and reflect on when you're in a leadership role. 👏

Comment below with some leadership techniques you are striving to be better at! 👇

node.text:
People want a voice in the decision-making! 📣 

As a leader, it is your duty to honor that, celebrate that, and intentionally practice that by allowing your team members to participate in those needle-moving conversations. When people feel like they have skin in the game, when they feel like they are actively contributing and a part of the creation, they will support you and your mission. 

You set the standard for what kind of team and communication will transpire. So be that positive example and influence for your team! Allow them a space to feel seen, heard, and appreciated for their ideas. 

That, my friends, is the defining duty and quality that separates a good leader from a GREAT one. 👏

node.text:
You might be getting a lot done, BUT…if you don’t feel aligned, you’re getting the WRONG things done. 

Listen — things are going to feel hard to you if they are not:

▶️ in alignment with your true passions and interests
▶️ bringing up curiosity and enthusiasm
▶️ filling you up when you’re doing it

So if you’re wondering why you just can’t get into something or you’ve lost your motivation, it’s not that something is wrong with you. Maybe something simply isn’t in alignment for you.

Think about it. Does that feel true?

Some #tuesdaythoughts for you, and cheering you on along the way. Your coach,
- Brendon.

#leadership #leadingothers #motivation #selfawareness #selfimprovement #selfgrowth #growthday #alignment #beinginalignment #passion #curiosity #enthusiasm

node.text:
So many people wander into their dreams, careers and goals without studying people who have already mapped the terrain and paved the way. They get lost for years—years of wasted efforts, frustrations and hardships that would have been avoided if they read some books, asked some questions, sought mentors, did a little research or made a few phone calls. 

The societal issue is we don’t have a culture of learning. 

The individual issue is people are afraid to ask questions and fear being seen starting small. Or, they just so much ego they think everyone else is an idiot or those who came before them are just old and boring.

There is nothing you want to do that doesn’t already have a roadmap and tons of mentors who could reveal a better way. 

Cheering on all to get a plan and mentor so you can achieve your dreams sanely and sooner.

Your coach,
Brendon.

#motivationalquotes #learning #thebrendonshow

You can do a lot of things. But it doesn’t mean you should. Choose wisely. 

When you are a high performing person, people will ask for help and put things on your plate. You’re skilled, and you could do it. But doing it and achieving it isn’t always the right thing to do. 

And sometimes you can climb a mountain… but it’s not worth it if it’s the wrong mountain.

Don’t do things just because you can. Do things that matter. 

Choose.
Wisely. 

Your coach,
Brendon.

Looking to revitalize the relationships you have with the people in your life? 🧐

One of the most powerful ways to do this is to find new ways to engage! What are some fun and new activities you can do together? Any new experiences you can share?

When people are in novelty situations, their self-awareness goes up! Their mindfulness goes up! Their attentiveness goes up!
